{SOUTH has 17 points counting 1 extra for the fifth \S. This is a middle-range hand with five \Ss. 
So he opens 1\S.

NORTH only has 7 points, 6 in high cards and one more for the doubleton \D. 
But she does have three \Ss, so she can respond 2\S.

Since SOUTH is middle-range, he makes one more try by bidding 3\S.

If NORTH had 9 or 10 points she would now bid 4\S - but with 7 she passes.}

